        <h1><a href="#why-is-climate-change-important"><i class="bi bi-hash"></i></a>Why is Climate Change important?</h1>
        Some facts about climate change is that the Earth's temperature has gone up by 0.08 degrees every decade since 1880, meaning that the Earth is getting warmer.<sup><a href="#citations-1">[1]</a></sup> Because of this, heat waves and wildfires would be more common, making it hotter.<sup><a href="#citations-4">[4]</a></sup> As a part of climate change, the Earth's average tempature is getting higher, and also changing what foods can be grown in certain areas.<sup><a href="#citations-3">[3, page 58]</a></sup> For example, farmers on the Canadian Praries used to not be able to grow corn there, because the climate wasn't warm enough to grow corn. Now, the climate on the Canadian Praries is warm enough to grow corn.
