        <h1><a href="#how-does-climate-change-affect-us"><i class="bi bi-hash"></i></a>How does Climate Change affect us?</h1>
        Climate change can affect many aspects of our life, like the clothes we wear. For example, people living in a cold climate would wear warm clothes, and people living in a warm climate would wear light clothes.<sup><a href="#citations-2">[2, page 46]</a></sup> Another example is that climate change will increace the chances of natural disasters, such as hurricanes, floods, and tornadoes.<sup><a href="#citations-2">[2, page 48]</a></sup> The climate can also affect what we consume by limiting the food that can be grown in an area.<sup><a href="#citations-1">[1]</a></sup><sup><a href="#citations-4">[4]</a></sup> For example, some foods can only grow in a certain climate, such as, pineapples only grow in tropical areas.
